    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#mohamed-jmr1997"/>, pp. 32-33 n. <citedRange>1 B</citedRange></bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>47.2177, B</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>085600</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
                <p>Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#dthorn-thorn2009"/>, p. <citedRange>266</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#belzic2022"/>, catalogue <citedRange>B.40</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Τέλων"><unclear>Τ</unclear>έλων</name> 
                        <persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Ἀνδρίας" type="patronymic">Ἀνδρία</name></persName></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p>
                    <app loc="1">
                        <rdg resp="#mohamed-jmr1997"><supplied reason="lost">Τ</supplied>έλων
                        <note>the upper bar is clear and a gamma should be excluded on prosopographical ground, see <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr085700</ref></note></rdg> 
                    </app>
.</p>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Télôn fils d'Andrias.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Telon son of Andrias.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Telon figlio di Andrias.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>This base comes from the same tomb, unrecorded by Cassels, as <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr085500</ref> and <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr085700</ref> and was
                    found during construction works in the new town of Shahat.</p>
                <p>Andrias the father, might be the man mentioned in <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr085500</ref> and Telon the father of Anaxippos mentioned in 
                    <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr085700</ref>.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
    </text>
